cs.GT, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.PF 

The paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to the problem of energy exchange between a smart grid and plug-in electric vehicle groups. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves optimization of revenue and charging strategies, which falls under the category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The use of variational inequalities and distributed algorithms suggests the involvement of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves simulations, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the economics of electric vehicle charging, which falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance).
